# Adding Skills — Cursor Only

When installing skills with the skills CLI (`npx skills add`), **always** target Cursor only so the skill is not installed for other agents (Cline, Codex, etc.).

## Command

Use the `--agent cursor` flag:

```bash
npx skills add <owner/repo@skill> --agent cursor -y
```

**Examples:**

```bash
npx skills add giuseppe-trisciuoglio/developer-kit@shadcn-ui --agent cursor -y
npx skills add vercel-labs/agent-skills@frontend-design --agent cursor -y
```

- **`--agent cursor`** — install only for Cursor (required).
- **`-y`** — skip confirmation prompts (optional).

Do **not** run `npx skills add <package> -y` without `--agent cursor`; that installs the skill for all detected agents.
